## 1.Declare an integer variable called likes and a pointer variable called ptrLikes; assign likes a value, point ptrLikes to likes, and print both the value and the address stored in ptrLikes.


```c
#include <stdio.h>

int main()
{
    int likes = 250;
    int *ptrLikes = &likes;

    printf("Value of likes = %d\n", likes);
    printf("Value using pointer = %d\n", *ptrLikes);
    printf("Address of likes = %p\n", (void *)&likes);
    printf("Address stored in ptrLikes = %p\n", (void *)ptrLikes);

    return 0;
}
```

**Sample Output:**

```
Value of likes = 250
Value using pointer = 250
Address of likes = 0x61ff08
Address stored in ptrLikes = 0x61ff08
```

