## 3.Given an array of 5 order amounts (e.g., Zomato orders), use a pointer to iterate through the array and print each amount along with its memory address.<br><br><em><strong>Hint:</strong> Use pointer arithmetic to move to the next element.</em>


```c
#include <stdio.h>

int main()
{
    int orders[5] = {250, 320, 180, 450, 390};
    int *ptr = orders;

    for (int i = 0; i < 5; i++)
    {
        printf("Order Amount = %d, Address = %p\n", *(ptr + i), (void *)(ptr + i));
    }

    return 0;
}
```

**Sample Output:**

```
Order Amount = 250, Address = 0x61ff00
Order Amount = 320, Address = 0x61ff04
Order Amount = 180, Address = 0x61ff08
Order Amount = 450, Address = 0x61ff0C
Order Amount = 390, Address = 0x61ff10
```

